By Ikenna Osuoha Association of Former Telecoms Employees of Nigeria (ATEN) says the modality for members to be paid their pensions and other entitlements is to register and be cleared by their chapter coordinators. Mrs Routa Musa, the National Adviser of the association, disclosed this in a statement issued in Abuja on Tuesday. Musa urged the members to identify themselves with some leaders that were introduced to Bureau of Public Enterprises (BPE) as representatives of the association. She listed the coordinators as Mr Gabriel Aremu, the President of the association; Mr Makinde Olusegun; the Secretary and Mrs Routa Musa, the National Adviser. Others are Mr James Icheme, the Chairman Realisation Committee and Mr Emmanuel Akawu Secretary Realisation Committee. She, however, commended President Muhammadu Buhari-led Federal Government for its commitment in the payment of pension and entitlements due to the telecom retirees. Musa assure of the association preparedness to achieve the desired goal of its members through collective efforts of all and collaboration with Bureau of Public Enterprise (BPE) and other relevant organisations. She commended the former and present leadership of the association for ensuring payment of pensions, reiterating their commitment to work in tune with the law. “ATEN has worked tremendously hard both in the past and present to ensure that the federal government pays us our pension buyouts and other entitlements. “This is according to the rule of law as granted by the liquidation court ruling of April, 2014.’’ Musa said. (NAN)